</title>
<subSubSection id="B8FAD834F7C8CD62877A88B50523F9B2" pageId="null" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph id="4471367E5DDFB4956CC5B9140C52DC5C" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">
Ausdauernd. 
<normalizedToken id="98CA58DC2B126822D30A518E381372F5" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="255B33B4561A6C671661BCAEE226F601" originalValue="radiär" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">radiaer</normalizedToken>
geteilt. 
<normalizedToken id="EF0505DDAA96AA06514BA1E46954834B" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">Blueten</normalizedToken>
aktinomorph, zwitterig. 
<emphasis id="43BB54E086D9BB329CFC607D5A7012DA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">
<normalizedToken id="2E30D8C521CBC33D16C180F968B1E5BB" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
5-15, 
<normalizedToken id="F5604ACA059F7786C6C0A463B3A216DC" originalValue="kronblattähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">kronblattaehnlich</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="FED1549D895CF55203AD27598A65EEA5" originalValue="Honigblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">Honigblaetter</normalizedToken>
klein
</emphasis>
(selten nicht vorhanden), 
<normalizedToken id="9DCA3013985D3C2C162FE4C575045A01" originalValue="spatelförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">spatelfoermig</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="B4CDE15E0464A8CCAE0B4298CDFD6E0B" originalValue="Staubblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">Staubblaetter</normalizedToken>
zahlreich. 
<emphasis id="9221583FF3D798AE325BF8F59F603194" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">Fruchtknoten zahlreich, mehrsamig</emphasis>
, mit kurzer, 
<normalizedToken id="1B362ECABB3B72D5154FD2A4C80FFE26" originalValue="schnabelförmiger" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">schnabelfoermiger</normalizedToken>
Narbe, meist mit 
<normalizedToken id="2E232E9D9619AE5F1B5EFBBCA708AA4B" originalValue="Drüsenhaaren" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">Druesenhaaren</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B9A3FAE40D013E9F4CE51CBABCA5737" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="3F06E6166A0362EA9FFE8F0C342E2C17" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="05B8FE7A4FA4B881C9E01855115681A2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Trollius</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="294DFAE4A0E19161C986ABD4E68700C0" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">umfasst</normalizedToken>
29 Arten;
</emphasis>
sie hat 
<emphasis id="7CB57C4EEB4D04CCE2B42CD05606FF49" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">eurasiatisch-nordamerikanische Verbreitung;</emphasis>
die meisten Arten sind in Ostasien. Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1965). In Europa einzig 
<emphasis id="6E90C7226F25E2D632D64EF79955F645" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="4EBA3B603391B4600AD7F1F8B367452C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="europaeus">T. europaeus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="783CAB4E992537737FA59469E4B095FF" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">
Polyploidie ist in der Gattung selten: von 14 Arten haben 13 2n = 16; 
<taxonomicName id="BC0D25C9761BD6FCAA7463446A161E50" authority="Muhl" authorityName="Muhl" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis id="CC418BA5FCFBC91568F8116ED933A984" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="37">T. americanus</emphasis>
Muhl
</taxonomicName>
, hat 2n = 32.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
